data.title: Great place for sandwich
data.text: I was up on a business trip. I really loved this place. They had unique sandwiches and a great service. It was in a good area and easy to get to. Parking is tough though..

data.title: Great dive bar and food!
data.text: This is a great little dive bar on Mass St. The whole menu is sandwiches but they are good! The TAC is amazing g, but get it with the bacon and salsa, you won't regret it! We had the quest dip too and it was such good comfort food! We will definitely be back.

data.title: Overpriced beer
data.text: Stopped in here around 11 last night (Sat night) and the place is a typical college hangout bar. Ordered a Boulevard Wheat that came in a small plastic cup for $6. What a ridiculous price for beer when you basically can go over to Free State and get much higher quality for $4.25. Soon after we arrived, they started charging a cover charge. For what? Your crappy jukebox music? Probably won't ever be back here.

data.title: Good food with friendly staff.
data.text: We went there for lunch, and I was pleasantly surprised. I was expecting generic bar food. I had a chicken wrap that was very good. Staff was very friendly and attentive, but it was not busy when we were there. Atmosphere: It is a basic bar that serves food, but the food was better than your average bar.

data.title: Not As Hopping As Columbia's
data.text: As a Mizzou alum, Quinton's has always been a staple. I checked out his Quinton's in hopes it would have the same vibe. It's an ok bar with decent drink specials, but not in a great location.

data.title: Nice setting for breakfast
data.text: Great place for breakfast. Fast service. Good food. Nice coffee selection. Prices are very reasonable.

data.title: Bar food.  Good bar food.
data.text: Really good bread bowl soup.  Sandwiches are just as good. Hit it early for lunch or past the lunch hour. Or, expect to wait.

data.title: Delicious Reubens
data.text: If you love reubens, here's one of the best places to get one. They have several varieties. I love getting the half sandwich w/ soup option. The soup comes out in a nice bread bowl, I usually get the potato soup - it comes w/ bacon sprinkled on top, the broccoli cheddar is also good.

data.title: Great Food
data.text: In town visiting KU.  We were told this was a must to try!  It did not disappoint!  Potato was delicious as was my deli sandwich!

data.title: Tasty Deli Sandwich Meets Hipster Bar W/Shredded Seating
data.text:
After reading previous reviews here we were a little leery about trying this place out but the online menu sounded like it had some unique tasty options and we were in the mood to try something new so we headed out to give it a shot. 
We arrived around 4:30 to a mostly empty restaurant. There were a couple of people seated at the bar and two to three other groups of people seated for a meal.
We were waited on quickly both for our drink and dinner options. We ordered the chips and queso appetizer and I ordered the Jayhawker Sandwich, Matt ordered the McQuinton. 
The Queso was very good, way better than the Espinaca Queso we had just the night before at Mi Ranchito! It had just enough of a kick to it...but not enough to burn your face off. The Jayhawker sandwich had a very unique Spicy honey mustard dressing and was so good! Matt enjoyed his McQuinton sandwich as well. We shared the queso and were able to take home half our sandwiches as leftovers.
The food was yummy and we look forward to coming back someday to try some of the bread bowl soups!
The atmosphere was more than a little confusing... The bar was really cool ....red and blue lighted for KU...well stocked. The building is old and has the typical stone walls you see in many of the downtown Mass St. buildings which of course has stand alone charm and appeal ...however...most of the seating in this restaurant is ripped up, badly. The food makes you feel like you are in a delicatessen, the bar makes you feel like you are in a hispter joint and the shredded seating everywhere makes you feel like you are in a college students dorm room or apartment after a particularly wild party.
Fixing the seating here should be relatively easy and fairly inexpensive and it would make the place look so much nicer.
The only other complaint we have is our waitress...Matt's drink ran dry. And though we asked for a box, (stop one) then she brought us a box and our ticket, (stop two)....she never asked him would he like a refill.
This unfortunately, is typical of service in Lawrence we have found. A big deduction for points in service as we believe we should never have to ask for a refill...especially in a bar!
That being said, we really enjoyed the meal and look forward to coming back sometime.
We definitely recommend this place for lunch or an EARLY dinner as we can see this is a college bar hangout later in the evening.

data.title: Same as it was in 2002
data.text: I went to The University of Kansas from 97-2002 and Quinton's was always one of my favorites. We were just their over Thanksgiving weekend and it was the same! Same bread bowl soup and sandwich combo, same atmosphere, and very friendly. Its a simple Sandwich place where you can stay and have a few drinks, or grab a quick lunch. We went a little early to beat the lunch rush, I recommend the BAC or the TAC and the Potato soup in a bread bow, and spicy chips. It turns more into a college bar after dinner so I would also recommend eating it at lunch.

data.title: Average all around
data.text: I've eaten here a couple times the last couple months, the sandwiches and soup are pretty good, but I've been pretty disappointed by the quality of their house salad each time (wilted, tasted like dirt).  Generally quick service, but the atmosphere could use a bit of updating.  Great drink specials though if you're looking for a quick drink.

data.title: Great Sandwich
data.text: Met some friends here for Beer and Deli and was pleasantly surprised.  Great selection of Deli Sandwiches and the meat is really piled high.  Was beyond expecation.  All of us loved our meal and the Chili is awesome.  Also try the Artichoke dip...you wont be disappointed

data.title: girls football weekend
data.text: We have eaten at Quintons several times throughout our years visiting KU. I was a little disappointed, they had a game day  menu, so wasn't full menu,but they did have quite  a few choices . It took our waitress a while to get to us and they weren't that busy yet. Food was good and a lot for value. Atmosphere was lacking a little, but had TVs going with sports  and still ok! Would go back. I had the Jayhawk  and it was very good!  Leah

data.title: Soup and Sandwiches
data.text: Fun lunch favorite of mine. The soups are so yummy!  The seating is limited so plan to arrive a little early. Good place for drinks with friends. Enjoy a brew and sandwich.

data.title: A big disappointment
data.text: This place used to be good and appreciated its customers.  The half sandwich and soup special was good and reasonably priced.  But my last visit was a plethora of disappointments.  First, the soup and sandwich special was overpriced, and to add insult to injury, it was half price for students only (and during Spring Break).  We even asked why they would discriminate against those who have kept the place in business for several years.  No good answer.  Apparently, they want to become a student dive.  I really don't think that will suffice during the summer.  The soup in the bread bowl was nothing special, nothing more than frozen restaurant supply soup.  And the lack of diners seemed to indicate my feelings are shared by others.  Don't think I will try them again.

data.title: Bar food plus
data.text:
Must haves at Quinton's:

Nachos
Any soup in a breadbowl (all cheesy/cream-based)
The Angel

I like to get their sandwich/soup combo so that I can have all of my favorites.  It's a great lunch spot, but not super fast so make sure you're not pressed for time, or if you are, that you let your waitress know.

data.title: Sandwich + Bread Bowl
data.text:
Quinton's is a must visit everytime my KU alum fiancee and I visit Lawrence. Can I just say-THE best spinach artichoke dip ever-so simple but so perfect!  

Of course their yummy bread bowl soups and aMAZing sandwiches are not to be forgotten. My fav is the Mangino on rye-tons of pastrami with swiss cheese, a sweet coleslaw, and a very tasty Russian mustard-love, love, love!  Get the 1/2 sandwich and breadbowl combo and you get a little taste of both!

data.title: Not a fan
data.text: Food is lackluster and not very well presented. I didn't expect much and it still didn't meet expectations.

data.title: Mostly student bar and grill
data.text: Average food, prices and services. Not convenient parking.
